<body>
    <h1>Proposal: Cross-Team Code Sharing Process</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-CurrentProcess">Cur=
rent Process</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Theory">Theory</h2>
<p>Perforce's linking functionality offers significant advantages over manu=
al copy-pasting when it comes to code sharing across multiple depots. With =
linking, teams can <strong>synchronize code across different depots seamles=
sly</strong>, ensuring that any updates made in one depot are automatically=
 reflected in the others without the need for redundant copying. This appro=
ach reduces the risk of inconsistent codebases, avoids duplication of effor=
t, and helps maintain a single source of truth for shared code.</p>
<p>By using depot imports, teams benefit from <strong>automatic updates</st=
rong> and the ability to integrate new features and fixes without manually =
transferring code between projects. This improves collaboration across team=
s and minimizes the chance of errors that can occur from outdated or mismat=
ched code versions.</p>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https=
://www.perforce.com/manuals/p4guide/Content/P4Guide/streams.paths.html" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://www.perforce.com/manuals/p4guide/Content/P4Guide/stre=
ams.paths.html</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Practice">Practice</h2>
<p>Stream specs enable teams to import depots directly, facilitating seamle=
ss updates and synchronization of code across different streams. This integ=
ration mechanism provides efficiency, flexibility, and streamlines the proc=
ess of incorporating changes into the project.</p><span class=3D"confluence=
-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size=
"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"image-202406=
21-005557.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"d74f4a8a8f968723d79882=
8584d115d16da47bda0aa9e169b605c0e7cffb8239" data-image-src=3D"https://offwo=
rldindustries.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/3354165251/image-2024=
0621-005557.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1718931359362&amp;cacheV=
ersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"819" data-width=3D"612" data-unreso=
lved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"3354099723" data-linked=
-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linke=
d-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20240621-005557.png" data-base-url=3D"htt=
ps://offworldindustries.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-ty=
pe=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"3354165251" data-link=
ed-resource-container-version=3D"1" data-media-id=3D"c6910055-2e44-4d59-8b1=
3-628084e64f25" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"625"></span>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-FeaturesofWorkwithIntegrati=
on">Features of Work with Integration</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Efficient Code Management:</strong> Integration through stream s=
pecs allows for efficient management of code changes and updates, reducing =
the risk of conflicts and ensuring consistency.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Flexibility in Development:</strong> Stream specs offer flexibil=
ity in organizing and sharing code across different streams, enabling flexi=
ble development workflows and collaboration between teams.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Streamlining Updates:</strong> With depot integration, teams can=
 easily receive updates and changes from upstream streams, facilitating an =
agile development process and enabling teams to adapt to evolving project r=
equirements.</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Challenges">Challenges</h2>
<p>However, in the course of working across multiple teams, we=E2=80=99ve e=
ncountered several issues stemming from <strong>uncommunicated or uncoordin=
ated changes</strong> to linked depots. These changes can lead to unexpecte=
d problems in builds, introduce bugs, and cause delays in delivery. Without=
 proper control and communication, even minor updates in one depot can disr=
upt other teams' work, resulting in cascading issues throughout the project=
.</p>
<p>To prevent these disruptions and maintain better control over the delive=
ry of our product, we propose a series of improvements to the process for m=
anaging stream specs and depot imports. These changes will allow us to reta=
in the flexibility and benefits of linking depots while ensuring that updat=
es are communicated, controlled, and seamlessly integrated into the develop=
ment workflow.</p>
<h1 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Proposal">Proposal</h1>
<p>To address these challenges and fully capitalize on the advantages of Pe=
rforce depot imports, I propose the following:</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-1.LeveragePerforceDepotImpo=
rtswithControlledUpdates">1. Leverage Perforce Depot Imports with Controlle=
d Updates</h3>
<p>Perforce=E2=80=99s depot imports are highly beneficial because they allo=
w for <strong>seamless synchronization of code</strong> across different st=
reams without manual copy-pasting. This reduces code duplication, minimizes=
 update conflicts, and enhances collaboration. However, to prevent unintend=
ed side effects, we need better control over how and when depots are import=
ed or updated across streams.</p>
<p>By enforcing <strong>read-only imports</strong> and requiring <strong>im=
ports changes to be made via the specified file</strong>, we can ensure tha=
t teams benefit from the integration while reducing risks of introducing bu=
gs or unexpected changes in builds.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-2.UseofspecifiedfileforStre=
amSpecChanges">2. Use of specified file for Stream Spec Changes</h3>
<p>Instead of allowing direct modifications to the Path field of stream spe=
cs, all changes should be made through the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</co=
de> file located in the depot's root. This structured approach will ensure =
that updates are controlled and transparent.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Automated Script Execution</strong>: Upon submission of the chan=
gelist, an automated script will apply the new specs to the stream. This sc=
ript will also run during builds and CI processes, ensuring consistent appl=
ication of stream specifications throughout development.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-3.CoordinationonReleaseBran=
ches">3. Coordination on Release Branches</h3>
<p>For depots that are linked, teams must coordinate the creation of releas=
e branches with other dependent teams. The <code>linked_depots.py</code> sc=
ript can help teams check which release branches are currently in use, allo=
wing for better planning and smoother handoffs between teams.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-4.AvoidLocksonChangelists">=
4. Avoid Locks on Changelists</h3>
<p>To avoid blocking child streams, we will discourage locking changelists =
in stream specs. Instead, teams should use older release branches or coordi=
nate new releases, allowing flexibility without disrupting other teams or b=
uilds.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-5.EnforceRead-OnlyDepotImpo=
rts">5. Enforce Read-Only Depot Imports</h3>
<p>All imported depots should be set to <strong>read-only</strong> mode (<c=
ode>import</code>) rather than read-write mode (<code>import+</code>). This=
 ensures that changes to linked depots are made in a controlled manner, red=
ucing the likelihood of build failures caused by unexpected modifications i=
n external depots.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Benefits">Benefits</h2>
<p>The proposed changes will offer significant advantages by combining the =
benefits of Perforce imports with improved control over depot management:</=
p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Seamless Updates with Controlled Integration</strong>: Teams can=
 easily synchronize code across depots while maintaining oversight, reducin=
g manual copy-pasting, and preventing unexpected conflicts.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Improved Coordination</strong>: Ensuring that teams communicate =
and coordinate when cutting off release branches prevents misalignment and =
unexpected project delays.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Automation for Consistency</strong>: Automated script execution =
ensures that stream specs are applied consistently across all development e=
nvironments, reducing build failures.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Flexibility without Risk</strong>: By discouraging changelist lo=
cking and enforcing read-only depot imports, teams can maintain flexibility=
 while ensuring that the integrity of linked depots is preserved.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-ImplementationPlan">Impleme=
ntation Plan</h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Adopt </strong><code>view_path_mappings.txt</code><strong>:</str=
ong> Update team processes and provide training to ensure that all stream s=
pec changes go through the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code> file.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p><strong>Automate Script Execution:</strong> Work with DevOps to ensure t=
he automated script for applying stream spec changes is integrated into the=
 Perforce server and CI pipeline.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Enforce Read-Only Depot Imports:</strong> Communicate and enforc=
e the policy of using <code>import</code> (read-only) depots for all extern=
al integrations.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Coordination on Release Branches:</strong> Ensure teams are awar=
e of the importance of coordinating release branches across linked depots, =
and encourage regular use of the <code>linked_depots.py</code> script.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>Avoid Changelist Locks:</strong> Update stream spec policies to =
prevent changelist locking and educate teams on how to create stable releas=
e branches without locking specs.</p></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p>This proposal emphasizes that while Perforce depot imports are a powerfu=
l tool for seamless updates and efficient collaboration, we must enforce st=
ricter controls to ensure project stability. By implementing these changes,=
 we can continue to benefit from efficient code integration while avoiding =
the risks of unexpected changes that lead to bugs and delivery delays. Cont=
rolled and well-coordinated use of depot imports will result in smoother bu=
ilds, fewer conflicts, and an overall improvement in project delivery timel=
ines.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-InstructionsForTheProposedP=
rocess">Instructions For The Proposed Process</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-WorkingwithStreamSpecsandLi=
nkedDepots">Working with Stream Specs and Linked Depots</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Restrictions">Restrictions<=
/h3>
<p><strong>Indirect Stream Specs Changing:</strong> To maintain consistency=
 and prevent unexpected issues, team members are restricted from directly m=
odifying the Views field of stream specs. Instead, any changes to stream sp=
ecs must be made indirectly through the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code>=
 file located in the depot's root directory.</p>
<p><strong>Read-Only Depot for Importing:</strong> When importing a depot, =
ensure that it is set to read-only (<code>import</code>) mode rather than r=
ead-write (<code>import+</code>). This prevents accidental modifications to=
 the imported depot, maintaining its integrity and ensuring that updates ar=
e controlled through stream specs and integration mechanisms.</p>
<p><strong>Avoiding Locks on Changelists:</strong> In stream specs, team me=
mbers must avoid locking on a changelist (<code>@&lt;#CL&gt;</code> attribu=
te) as it can disrupt child streams and cannot be overridden. Instead, use =
older release branches or coordinate the creation of a new release to avoid=
 conflicts and maintain project stability.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-ProcedureforModifyingStream=
Specs">Procedure for Modifying Stream Specs</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Update </strong><code>view_path_mappings.txt</code>: To modify t=
he stream specifications, edit the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code> file=
 in the root directory of the depot.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Include Changes in a Changelist (CL):</strong> After updating th=
e <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code> file, create a new changelist (CL) th=
at includes these changes.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Submit the Changelist:</strong> Submit the changelist containing=
 the updates to the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code> file.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Automated Script Execution:</strong> Upon submission, an automat=
ed script will run on the Perforce server. This script applies the changes =
from the <code>view_path_mappings.txt</code> file to the stream specs, ensu=
ring that the modifications are accurately reflected.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Build and Continuous Integration (CI) Integration:</strong> Addi=
tionally, the script to apply the <code>view_path_mappings</code> specs wil=
l be executed during builds and CI processes. This ensures that the stream =
specifications are consistently applied across different stages of developm=
ent, further enhancing project stability and consistency.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-ImportanceofControlledChang=
es">Importance of Controlled Changes</h3>
<p>Controlled changes to stream specifications are crucial for project stab=
ility. Direct modifications to stream specs can lead to unexpected issues a=
nd conflicts within the project structure. By enforcing the use of <code>vi=
ew_path_mappings.txt</code>, we ensure better control and minimize the risk=
 of disruptions to the project workflow.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-ProvidingaDepotforIntegrati=
ng">Providing a Depot for Integrating</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-CoordinationonReleaseBranch=
es">Coordination on Release Branches</h3>
<p>Team members working with depots that will be linked must coordinate the=
 cutting off of release branches. This coordination is essential to ensure =
that all teams using the depot are aware of the changes and can adjust thei=
r workflows accordingly.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-Usinglinked_depots.pyScript=
">Using <code>linked_depots.py</code> Script</h3>
<p>To facilitate the management of release branches and ensure alignment ac=
ross teams, team members can utilize the <code>linked_depots.py</code> scri=
pt. This script allows users to check which release branches are currently =
in use and helps streamline the coordination process.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">python =
linked_depots.py &lt;depot_name&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Examples:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$ pytho=
n linked_depots.py ODK/Plugins/Clans
Connected to Perforce server
Disconnected from Perforce server
Depots linked to the current depot:
//ODK/Projects/CodeSandbox/Main
//ODK/Projects/DevSandbox/Main
//Yakisoba/0.8.0
//Yakisoba/[TR-3152]_Clans_implementation
//Yakisoba/Main</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$ pytho=
n linked_depots.py ODK/Plugins/Core/v1.0.2
Connected to Perforce server
Disconnected from Perforce server
Depots linked to the current depot:
//PersonalProjects/AnalyticsSample/VersioningTest
//Squad/Main
//Squad44/Game/Main
//Squad44/Game/SQ44_ODK</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Proposal:Cross-TeamCodeSharingProcess-BestPractices">Best Practic=
es</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Regularly communicate and coordinate with teams using linked depots to e=
nsure smooth transitions and minimize disruptions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Prioritize stability and consistency when making changes to stream specs=
 or release branches.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Utilize automated scripts and tools provided to streamline processes and=
 maintain project integrity.</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
